\textbf{Step 1: Understand the magnetic force in a magnet's poles.}

Magnetic forces always act between magnetic poles. A north pole (N) attracts a south pole (S) and repels another north pole. A south pole (S) also attracts a north pole (N) and repels another south pole.

\textbf{Step 2: Analyze Pair 1: The top magnet is a north pole, and the bottom magnet is a south pole.}

The north pole of the top magnet and the south pole of the bottom magnet attract each other.

